    "body": "Hi!\r\n\r\nI was testing:\r\n```php\r\n$wa->SendPresenceSubscription($dst);\r\n```\r\nAn async function that show us when the target is 'available' or 'unavailable'. Oks.\r\nI used this:\r\n```php\r\nfunction onPresenceReceived($username, $from, $type)\r\n{\r\n    echo $type;\r\n}\r\n...\r\n$wa->eventManager()->bind(\"onPresence\", \"onPresenceReceived\");\r\n```\r\nBut... Here is the/my problem, when the user goes offline:\r\n\r\n```\r\nrx  <presence from=“34*********@s.whatsapp.net\" type=\"unavailable\"></presence>\r\n```\r\nSo $type is 'unavailable'\r\n\r\nHere, when the user goes online:\r\n```\r\nrx  <presence from=“34*********@s.whatsapp.net\"></presence>\r\n```\r\nIt wont assign a value to $type.\r\n***[Update]:*** Also, it seems that when the user goes online, its not linked to the onPresence event, but why? Is there other way to detect that presence (when the user goes online)?\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2014-06-03T14:37:58Z",
